727021f-a.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - 138th Street
727021f-a.text:
Jamaica Avenue, south side, at 138th Street, viewing
eastward across the latter. View 1 shows several buildings
near the southwest corner of the two thoroughfares; view 2
is east aoross the clearance at the corner; view 3 shows the
N.E. corner.
P. L. Sperr  May 8, 1934
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Viewa 1,2,3

725858f-c.title: Queens: 138th Street - Jamaica Avenue
725858f-c.text:
138th Street, east side, north of Ninetieth to Jamaica Aves.
(elevated line thereon), showing in a set of four'views the C. Carl
house of 1860. J.M. McCauley was the owner in 1873; and Wm. Danmar
from 1902 to 1934. This house was erected by a member of the Royal
Scotch Stuart family about 1780. The walls of this house are twenty-
two inches thick filled with brick; the shutters outside and inside
were barricaded with iron bars. A wing detached, once a part of this
house, situated in rear thereof, was used as a carpenter shop. It
was demolished on April 5, 1934.
1923.
View 2: April 1923.
View 3: 1922.
View 4: April 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
